ShortDescription:
Furnished Rooms For a single person or groups.  walking distance to Cornell  University.
Corner of Eddy St. & Buffalo St. 
- Aug., 2025
LongDescription:
Furnished Rooms For a single person or groups. 
Corner of Eddy and Buffalo Street. 
A well maintained large house. 
Walking distance to Cornell University. 

Rent: $715/mo or $795/mo depending on room size.

All utilities and garbage disposal included. 
5 baths, 1 big kitchen. 
Cleaning service provided for common areas. 
Laundry on premises.

Available 8/10/2024, 12 months lease. 

Pls TEXT: Sharon 929 538 9073 (cell); 
www.gooderealtyco.com to view floor plan

ShortDescription: Recently renovated( see pictures) pet friendly,large 350 square foot studio apartment,with full kitchen and bath, 6 minutes to vet school.
LongDescription: Many veterinarian and grad students live here in this small quiet complex of 24 units. All have walk out access to a spacious 2.5 acre grounds located across the road from Fall creek. Trash, parking, water and sewer, professional  and courteous maintenance provided by the owner of 22 years, included in the rent on this updated studio apartment . Laundry on site , and bus service available. Rent w/o pets $820.00 mo, $845.00 with pets.

ShortDescription: Renovated House available near Campus AUG 2025
LongDescription:
House available starting 8/8/2025 - 7/31/2026. 10 min walk to campus. Bus stop around corner. No smoking or pets. Accepting single applicants or applications for groups of friends. 
Includes:
- Furnished rooms with bed, dresser, desk
- Furnished living room and study room
- 2 renovated bathrooms 
- New kitchen appliances
- Free laundry in basement

Internet & utilities not included. Video tour available. Email for questions. More details: www.ferrisplacerentals.com

ShortDescription:
GEM OF A PLACE    NEAR THE VET SCHOOL
AVAILABLE May 1, 2025 
2 BDRM
LongDescription: The bottom part of a house with a separate entrance- light and bright and not at all basement-y. Newer kitchen and plenty of room. In a quiet, beautiful country setting near the state forest. Is well maintained and has a propane stove to keep you cozy in the winter, new washer and dryer and flooring. The apartment is centrally located: the Commons is nine miles; Dryden/TC3 is approximately six miles and Cornell is eight miles. Come make it your home. Non-smoking/vaping and pets upon approval.

ShortDescription: Beautiful 1 bedroom apt surrounded by lawn and gardens in Cayuga Heights. It's on several TCAT bus routes: 2 miles to Cornell campus. The rent includes internet, hot water and utilities. Free parking.

ShortDescription: Beautiful Downtown home - Grad. or PhD. Students/Professor. Same block with TCAT bus to Cornell (in minutes), and the Cascadilla Gorge.  Walk path to Cornell & Only 2 blocks to Downtown! ONE SPACE NOW
LongDescription: Best located Historic Home in Ithaca for lease. Next to downtown, the Cascadilla Gorge, walking trail and T-CAT bus to Cornell. The Private Bedroom, Bath & common salon,  living areas, kitchen, porch was once a former Tibetan Monastery, then a yoga studio with plenty of light, and wooden floors.  The Gorge behind house can be heard from the expansive private patio. $1195 includes cable, internet; water, kitchen/dinning, private room, bathroom, common areas, furnishings.

ShortDescription:
Very nicely fully furnished nonsmoking 1BR / 1Ba 400ft2  
All utilities included including high speed internet. $1700/mo + cost for couple. Excellent credit, references required Lease may be extended.
LongDescription: 9-12 mo Very nicely furnished apartment, not your typical student furniture with a very good mattress. Super quiet location 4 mi East of Cornell and Vet School, located next to Cornell woods with spring-fed brook running next to the apartment. All utilities included. Shared laundry. Excellent credit and references necessary, verification of 3x rental income plus first, last and security deposit due at signing. Lease term 9-12 months with option to extend. Add cost if rented to a couple.

ShortDescription: 3 BR/1 BA Serene, 1.3 acre park-like setting. Spacious well-kept unit in Mid-Century ranch, 2.3 mi / 5 min to CU Vet College. Near bus stop. 2 - 3 tenants. WIFI-6. Pets o.k. Lower level apt available.
LongDescription:
Large Living Rm, Separate Dining Rm. Ample closets, pantry, & built-in shelves. 3rd BR / study. W/D on premises; Zone heat & A/C. Emergency Generator. Partially furnished. 
Rent incl: Off-street parking, Water, Sewer, Lawn Care, Snow Removal & Wkly Trash & Recycling Svc.
Plus Gas & Electric: fair-shared w/ lower unit.
Deposit(s): Security and Pet (per landlord approved pet, max 2 pets / apt) due at signing. Just minutes to the Rail Trail, Monkey Run Natural Area & Fall Creek. Peaceful.

ShortDescription: Lovely  1 BR plus study apartment in home; 5-7 minute walk  to Collegetown, Law School on Main Campus in family neighborhood. Perfect fo serious law student who hopes to make Law Journal!

If you want to succeed in your studies, live in a nice environment with landlord whom you know and trust to repair any problems as they arise, 224 Bryant is for you.

ShortDescription: Available now: 1 bdrm in beautiful Cayuga Heights home, walk to campus, and $800/month (utilities included). Only other resident is owner, who has a small dog that resides in her section of home.

Great opportunity for grad student, post-doc, or young professional. Furnished 1 bedroom. Free driveway parking, on bus route, and separate outside entrance. Sheets, blankets, comforter and towels, along with utilities, cable, wi-fi, TV, air conditioning, etc. are included. Tenant has own bathroom and small office. Kitchen is shared...will discuss. The living room area is very rarely used by owner. In a student populated and friendly neighborhood.

One of the best deals you can find in Ithaca.

ShortDescription: Beautiful Downtown Bedroom -SOON Avail Grad., PhD. Students/Professor. Same block with TCAT bus to Cornell, and Cascadilla Gorge. Walk path to Cornell. Only 2 blocks to Down Town! Furnished & Classy.
LongDescription:
Best located Historic Home in Ithaca for You & Your Family for lease. 
One of the first built homes in the city, this home was also once selected as the first Monastery in Ithaca for Tibetan Monks, while the separate upstairs apartment served as a yoga studio. 
Jacuzzi & updated bathrooms; Hard wood floors throughout, open kitchen and granite table dining, 3-common large spaces w/ beautiful furniture, expansive patio for entertaining with sound of the waterfalls behind you, and more!

LongDescription: Rent is $594/mo, plus ~$40/mo for utilities. Optional parking for $10/mo. There is also coin-operated laundry, a spacious backyard, and an attic for extra storage. This 4-bedroom, 2.5-bathroom residence boasts a modern, contemporary design. The kitchen features top-of-the-line appliances and seamlessly opens to the dining and living areas. The first floor includes an office and a convenient half bathroom. With a 2-car attached garage and a spacious basement offering ample storage, you'll also find a high-efficiency washer and dryer.

ShortDescription: 2 bedroom in Victorian in Dewitt Park Historic District
LongDescription: Large 2nd-floor unfurnished two-bedroom apartment in a Victorian house in the Dewitt Park Historic District. Owners live on the first floor and are, responsible landlords who are respectful of your privacy.

These spacious single-family homes boast 5 bedrooms, 4 baths, and a garage, seamlessly blending comfort with the serene beauty of upstate New York.

ShortDescription: Motivated sublet! Entire apartment in The Ithacan. 1 bed, 1 bath + office, furnished. Stainless steel, W/D, walk-in closet. Rooftop terrace, gym, business lounge. Available to June 2025.
LongDescription:
Avoid a 12-month lease and save on summer rent! Take over my furnished 1BR/1BA Ithacan Residences sublet until June 2025. Rent will range from $2000-2900/month depending on lease start date. Enjoy in-unit washer/dryer, stainless steel appliances, walk-in closet, and a flexible office space. Building boasts rooftop terrace, gym, business lounge, and more.
In-unit laundry. The apartment is located on the 8th floor, ensuring ample natural light as it's positioned above the adjacent parking garage.

ShortDescription:
Fall 2025 Sublet - $1300/month
Single Bedroom in a 6 Bedroom 2 Bathroom Unit
118 College Avenue Unit 401 (Collegetown)
LongDescription:
Hi, I'm looking for someone to sublease my room in a 6 bedroom 2 bathroom apartment in Collegetown for Fall 2025 Semester with 5 upperclassmen male housemates.

- Utilities Included (electricity/gas/water/wifi)
- Fully Furnished (including 2 living room couches and TV, full size bed, desk, chair, and drawers)
- Washer/Dryer in Unit 
- Spacious Well-Lit Living Room
- Modern Kitchen (with a dishwasher)
- Private Balcony
- Street Parking or Paid Lot Parking

Contact me for more information!

ShortDescription: FOR RENT Don't miss out on this Super Energy Efficient-Passive Solar Contemporary  Designed 4 Bedroom, 1.5 bath Townhouse with Washer and Dryer in Townhouse. All appliances are General Electic.
LongDescription: features a solar green house with trombe-wall, 6" thick concrete slab, ventilating skylights, thermal insulated glass. Double-entry airlock foyer off concrete landing.  Kitchen has working breakfast bar. French doors, private patio. Waterford cast iron wood stove burning fireplace. Landlord/Owneris a NYSE-licensed Broker.

Lots of natural lighting.

ShortDescription: Room available for sublet until May 18, 2025 in furnished Ithaca home, walking distance from Cornell's campus and Ithaca Commons. Renovated kitchen with stainless appliances, heat, A/C, and laundry.
LongDescription:
Sublet is for one beautifully furnished, light-filled bedroom and shared common space, including kitchen, living room, family room, dining room, and sunroom. Tall ceilings, classic Victorian details, formal entry, & Lodge-style sunroom. Distant views of West Hill from all three stories.

Wooden fencing encloses the backyard with stone patio and kitchen garden.

Email current Cornell graduate student at jab865@Cornell.edu.

Subject to landlord approval. Friendly dog on premises some of the time.

ShortDescription: Llenroc Mansion Student Housing (Cornell West Campus)
LongDescription:
Llenroc Welcomes Cornell students for 2025-2026

Llenroc (Cornell spelled backwards) is Ezra Cornellâ€™s historic mansion located at 100 Cornell Avenue, just minutes from Cornell University's West Campus.

The mansion has historically been the home of the Delta Phi fraternity, but it is now open for leasing to Cornell University students for the 2025-2026 academic year.

Single room rates start at $14236 for a 9 month academic year lease. Double and triple occupancy rates are available.

ShortDescription: 5 Bed 1.5 bath, Student House ALL utilities and parking for 5+ included, 10 month/accedemic school year lease
LongDescription: 809 South Aurora is a 5 bedroom, one and a half bath house.  This property includes a washer and dryer, dishwasher, garbage, parking for 5+ vehicles and snow removal.  All utilities (heat, water, electric) are included and trash facilities are available.  This is a single family house with a private parking lot for 5+ cars. 809 is about a 5 minute walk to IC, 10 minute walk downtown, 10 minute car ride to Cornell and located on a main bus line.

ShortDescription: 1 br on north campus available ASAP! Flexible lease takeover
LongDescription: Looking for someone to takeover a 1 br lease at Brooklane apartments. My current lease is through mid July, but leasing is happy to work with a new tenant on a lease starting ASAP and continuing as long as you need it for. It is a SUPER convenient location on the corner of 3 TCAT stops, a 7 minute walk to campus, and a very short walk to the C2C north campus pickup spot. In-building laundry facility and recently renovated wood floors in-unit. Semi-furnished or unfurnished depending on your needs

ShortDescription: Sunny house. Ideal for family or professional. Off of East Hill Trail, 20' walk to Cornell.
LongDescription:
20' walking to Cornell. Large living room area with lots of light and fireplace. Two bedrooms and a sunroom that works equally well as an office or additional bedroom. Master bedroom with large walk-in closet and bathroom en-suite. Two fully equipped bathrooms and a fully renovated kitchen with stainless steel appliances and quartz countertops. 
New washer and dryer and storage in our laundry room. Two-car covered parking, snow removal and water included. Belle Sherman school district.

ShortDescription: Old House with high ceilings, bulit in 1902. Graduate Students preferred.  3 bedrooms for 3 unrelated tenants. It has two off-street parking. Quiet yet convenient location. real hardwood floors.
LongDescription: The apartment has 3 bedrooms for 3 unrelated tenants. It has two off-street parking space. New cooking stove, new furnace, new hot water boiler.  Laundry (washer and dryer) on site in basement for usage by tenants of the house only.  It is a rather rare unit in downtown, the same block with Gimme Coffee! Landlord lives in Florida but accessible via e-mail, internet. Apt-2 tenants can use huge attic space for extra storage. APT-2 has an attic, contributed to many thesis and dissertations.

ShortDescription: We are two third year PhD students in Social Sciences, looking for a roommate to share an apartment in the village of Cayuga Heights (north of Ithaca, Highland Road) for the 2025-2026 academic year.
LongDescription:
The apartment is very well located! It's just an 18-minute walk from campus, in a very quiet area. Two bus lines (32 and 30) have stops nearby. It's easy to get to campus, college town or downtown using either of these lines. Line 32 goes straight down to central campus in 7 minutes. There's plenty of on-street parking nearby if you have a car.
The apartment has a spacious kitchen and a fairly large living room with a TV and comfortable sofas. Cleanliness is a must for us.

ShortDescription: 572 Warren Rd. Quiet lg home on 2 acres.5min drive to Cornell and 2min walk to TCAT! Free parking. All-inclusive rent (utils, WiFi). Community printer and computer. Routine cleaning service.
LongDescription: Quiet furnished home @ 572 Warren Rd (~2 acres). 5min drive/2min walk TCAT to Cornell. Welcoming to all! Rms $665-850 (vary: size/bath/lease). Rent INCLUDES: ALL utils, high-speed WiFi, common area cleaning, free laundry, free parking, grounds maint, house computer/printer! Shared: well-equipped kitchen (2 fridges), 3 decks, living/dining rms, lounge & study areas. Contact us for a rental application!

ShortDescription: One bedroom apartment, entire first floor of duplex.  On bus line downtown, close to everything. Avail June or July.
LongDescription: Large bedroom, full bathroom, full kitchen, large living room. Private entry. Hardwood & ceramic tile flooring. Unfurnished. Avail 1st July for 12 mo lease, or move-in in June for 13 mo w reduced June rent. Tenant pays gas, electric, garbage, internet/cable. Legal for one person or couple. On bus route, close to many amenities: shopping, dining, entertainment. Curbside parking, & shared driveway. No smoking. Pet allowed upon review/approval, with non-refundable fee.

ShortDescription: This house is located in the heart of Collegetown, a 5 min walk to campus. One bedroom available. Plenty of room for study, sleep, and storage plus two full ceramic bathrooms and two open kitchens.
LongDescription: This room is a part of a 7-person house, with 2 floors--each having its own kitchen, bathroom, and common living area with multiple couches. You'll be living with 6 seniors at Cornell (male) who are clean, laidback, and friendly. The room, which is located on the first floor along with 3 other rooms, comes furnished with a bed, desk, chair, and dresser. There are also laundry machines and a dishwasher located within the house. Rent is $965/month for a 12-month lease.

ShortDescription: 1 bedroom rental in a 5 bedroom shared LUX & LOFT apartment in the heart of Collegetown. It is the closest convenience for off-campus housing to the Cornell Campus. Start Date: January 1,2026
LongDescription: The bedroom is fully furnished with a private bathroom.
